patgen Description

patgen is a simple pattern generator designed to build and run on Linux 
platforms and embedded Linux platform. Requires stadard c library. To run the 
default font needs to be a symbolically linked to the run directory. GPL font,
K1FS-1.2, is included as the default. "DejaVuSansMono.ttf" has also been
tested. The DejaVu font can be found in /usr/share/fonts/truetype on yocto
systems or in /usr/share/fonts/truetype/dejavu on ubuntu systems.

patgen is not intented to replace other GPU and VPU media tests. It is inteded
to provide tools to isolate an debug display issues.  

patgen.exe  [-v] [-d] [-h] [-a alpha percent ] [-border] [-header] 
[-c xRGB pixel value 0xrrggbb] [-vs -vsize widthxheight pixels]
[-i intensity percent] [-size checker size pixels]
[-steps number of graybar steps] [-pix_fmt pixel format]
[-r rotation 0,90,180,or 270 degrees] [-min_i min_intensity percent]
[-max_i max_intensity percent] [-o outfile name prefix] [-p pattern]
[-s stride pixels]


usage: ./patgen.exe
	-v -verbose
		Echo the command parameters

	-d -debug [level]
		Sets the debug level

	-p -pattern [pattern]
		Select the type pattern to generate:
		checker		creates a checkerboard pattern using -size

		circle		Draw circle with a background fill
		colorbar	Vertical color bars
		colorbar2	Alternate colors bars
		colorcheck	24 color checker
		fill		Fill the pattern with -color at -intensity).
		font		Pattern with some sample text from the fonts in use.
		graybar		11 shaded bars, the default is white bars from
				100% to 0%. The -color, -steps, -min_i, and max_i
				parameters can be used with this pattern.
		gradient	Creates four horizontal gradient bars red,
				green , blue and white.

		vgradient	Creates four vertical gradient bars red, green,
				blue, and white.
		hsv		Creates an HSV color transtion gradient. The
				-i sets the V (value) for HSV.
		test		Creates a testcard like pattern.

		wheel	Creates an HSV color wheel. The -i sets the V
			(value) for HSV.

	-border
		Adds a border to the patern

	-header
		Adds header text to the pattern border

	-footer
		Adds footer text to the pattern border

	-a -alpha [alpha (%)]
		Sets the alpha value. Default is 100.0%

	-c -[RGB color in hex 0xaarrbbgg]
		Sets the color default for the fill and
		graybar patterns. Default is white.

	-i -intensity [intensity (%)]
		Sets the color intensity for the colorbar, fill and
		hsv patterns. Default is 100.0%

	-min_i [minimum intensity (%)] 
		Sets the minimum intensity for the graybar pattern. Default is 0.0%

	-max_i[maximum intensity (%)]
		Sets the maximum intensity for the graybar pattern. Default is 100.0%

	-steps [steps]
		Sets the number steps in the graybar pattern

	-size  -checker_size [size (pixels)]
		Sets the size of the checker board squares in pixels

	-o -outfile [prefix string]
		Adds a prefix to the default pattern name

	-pix_fmt
		Supported formats are:
			bgra     32 bits per pixel RGB
			rgb565le 16 bits per pixel RGB
			yuv444p  24 bits per pixel YUV (3 planes Y, U and V)
			yuv420p  12 bits per pixel YUV (3 planes Y, U and V)
			nv12     12 bits per pixel YUV (2 planes Y and UV)

	-vs -vsize [HxW (pixelsxpixels] Sets the width and hight of the output

	-r -rotation [rotation (degrees)] rotates the final image to 0, 90, 180, or 360

	-stride [stride (pixels)] Sets the stride if it is larger the the width

	-fb [frame buffer device] Name of the framebuffer device file

